<subSubSection lastPageId="33" lastPageNumber="34" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,1969,2032]" lastBlockId="33.[151,1437,151,322]" lastPageId="33" lastPageNumber="34" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
This genus has brachypronotal and macropronotal specimens in the unique species known: 
<taxonomicName authority="Bolivar, 1887" authorityName="Bolivar" authorityYear="1887" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Puiggaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="antennata">
<emphasis box="[1201,1436,1970,1995]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Puiggaria antennata</emphasis>
Bolívar, 1887
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[331,421,2005,2031]" captionStart="FIGURE 27" captionStartId="34.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[170,1417,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-22@34.[170,1417,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURE 27. Puiggaria antennata Bolívar, 1887 allotype (A) left lateral view, (B) dorsal view, (C) frontal view, highlighting the scutellate frontal structure (as shield-shaped) and (D) labels. Scale bar = 5 mm. Photo of type:Academy of Natural Sciences of Drexel University, Philadelphia/Daniela Silva and Marcelo Pereira." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4614448" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4614448/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Fig. 27</figureCitation>
). It is characterized by fastigium not reaching the most anterior surface of the eyes; antennae with 20-22 segments; anterior margin of the pronotum (lateral and dorsal view) hook-like (median carina sharply cristate); mid femur apical spine presence and the exclusive characteristic among the batrachideines: frontal costa and fascial carinae (frontal view) widely divergent, forming a scutellate frontal structure (as shield-shaped) (
<figureCitation box="[160,263,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 27" captionStartId="34.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[170,1417,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-22@34.[170,1417,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURE 27. Puiggaria antennata Bolívar, 1887 allotype (A) left lateral view, (B) dorsal view, (C) frontal view, highlighting the scutellate frontal structure (as shield-shaped) and (D) labels. Scale bar = 5 mm. Photo of type:Academy of Natural Sciences of Drexel University, Philadelphia/Daniela Silva and Marcelo Pereira." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4614448" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4614448/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Fig. 27C</figureCitation>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Grant Jr., H. J." box="[290,430,258,285]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" pagination="67 - 108" refId="ref22611" refString="Grant Jr., H. J. (1956) The taxonomy of Batrachidea, Puiggaria, Lophoscirtus, Eutettigidea and Rehnidium n. gen. (Orthotpera: Acridoidea, Tetrigidae). Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 82, 67 - 108." type="journal article" year="1956">Grant, 1956</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Grant, H. J." box="[444,504,259,286]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" refId="ref22659" refString="Grant, H. J. (1962) A revision of the subfamily Batrachideinae (Orthoptera; Tetrigidae). PhD Thesis, University of Colorado Library, University of Colorado, Colorado, 208 pp." type="book" year="1962">1962</bibRefCitation>
). The distribution is known in Southern 
<collectingCountry box="[976,1044,259,285]" name="Brazil" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Brazil</collectingCountry>
from the States of Matto Grosso, 
<collectingRegion box="[151,230,295,321]" country="Brazil" name="Parana" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Paraná</collectingRegion>
, Santa Catharina, S„o Paulo (
<bibRefCitation author="Grant Jr., H. J." box="[563,699,294,321]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" pagination="67 - 108" refId="ref22611" refString="Grant Jr., H. J. (1956) The taxonomy of Batrachidea, Puiggaria, Lophoscirtus, Eutettigidea and Rehnidium n. gen. (Orthotpera: Acridoidea, Tetrigidae). Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 82, 67 - 108." type="journal article" year="1956">Grant, 1956</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Grant, H. J." box="[710,767,295,322]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" refId="ref22659" refString="Grant, H. J. (1962) A revision of the subfamily Batrachideinae (Orthoptera; Tetrigidae). PhD Thesis, University of Colorado Library, University of Colorado, Colorado, 208 pp." type="book" year="1962">1962</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<collectingCountry box="[830,934,295,321]" name="Paraguay" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
(Horqueta) (
<bibRefCitation author="Grant, H. J." box="[1080,1215,295,322]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" refId="ref22659" refString="Grant, H. J. (1962) A revision of the subfamily Batrachideinae (Orthoptera; Tetrigidae). PhD Thesis, University of Colorado Library, University of Colorado, Colorado, 208 pp." type="book" year="1962">Grant, 1962</bibRefCitation>
) (
<figureCitation box="[1239,1323,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURE 37" captionStartId="45.[151,250,1959,1983]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,990,1935]" captionTargetId="figure-39@45.[151,1436,990,1936]" captionTargetPageId="45" captionText="FIGURE 37. Map of approximated occurrence of the genera Puiggaria Bolívar, 1887; Halmatettix Hancock, 1909; Lophoscirtus Bruner, 1910 and Paurotarsus Hancock, 1900." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4614468" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4614468/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Fig. 37</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
